    "body": "> You are welcome to open a PR with a better phrasing. Unfortunately, `cannot process future transaction currently` is _not_ better, IMO: it is very vague (doesn't tell us what the problem is), and it is not really correct either.\r\n> \r\n> We don't need to have a ticket open for just poor phrasing, so I'll close this. Cheers!\r\n\r\nI see your point here. Will open a PR. My point is, that the current message is plain wrong, as there really is no pending TX which would be replaced. \r\n\r\nStill - I'll probably need some input in order to identify the real possible reasons for the dismissal of new TX with `ErrFutureReplacePending`.",
